-- TNK-BP in Talks to Buy Two Itera Oil Fields, Kommersant Says
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-05-31T06:30:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/tnk-bp-in-talks-to-buy-two-itera-oil-fields-kommersant-says.html
TNK-BP, the Russian oil producer
half-owned by  BP Plc (BP/) , is in talks with OOO Itera to buy two oil
fields in the Orenburg region,  Kommersant  reported, citing an
unidentified person at the gas explorer.  The two fields are valued at about $100 million and could
together produce as much as 400,000 metric tons of crude a year,
or 8,000 barrels a day, Kommersant said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
